description:
FOLLOW THE EXCITING ADVENTURES OF LADY LIBERTY, SPECIAL AGENT TO LOUIS XVI !

Did you know that one of the greatest national epics began with the secret wars of Louis XVI's spies during the American Revolution? Did you know that the most formidable of these spies was a woman? And that woman was called Lady Liberty!
name: Le Secret du Roi

description:
The wind of change is going to take Lady Liberty to the thirteen colonies. The American settlers dream of freedom, and she will bring them Revolution.

To avenge her mother, Lya de Beaumont swore to make Louis XVI and George III lose their crowns. A wind of revolution is beginning to blow over the world. A wind that will make the Sally Brown’s sails billow and take Lya, Lady Gage and the intriguer Beaumarchais towards the colonies. Rebellious America has become a powder keg and only needs a spark to light it. And Lya is the spark!
name: Treize colonies

description:
First episode of the Aérospostale series, dedicated to Guillaumet

June 13, 1930. Colina base, smack in the middle of the Andes.

Henri Guillaumet, an experienced Aéropostale pilot, doesn't know it but is taking off straight for hell. Caught in a violent storm, his plane crashes in the middle of the snowcaps. Miraculously unharmed, he hopes he will quickly be found by his companions, especially since he is running low on supplies. But after 3 days of useless hope, he decides to make his way to Argentina. Then starts a journey of over 70 km. From breathtaking falls to intense exhaustion, the 70 km trek will be long, Guillaumet will only keep going because of one thought: “I will save my own skin!”
name: Guillaumet

description:
SECOND PART DEDICATED TO JEAN MERMOZ, THE LEGEND OF THE AEROPOSTALE

May 12th 1930, Jean Mermoz who left from Saint-Louis-du-Senegal tries to cross the south Atlantic on the Laté 28 baptised the “Count of La Vaulx”.

He is far from thinking that he will have to face on of the biggest tests of his illustrious pilot career: a “convergence zone”, a huge mass of dark clouds that cover the entire ocean and terrorizes many sailors...
name: Mermoz

description:
THE STORY OF THE AVIATOR PAUL VACHET, VERITABLE PIONEER OF AIR TRANSPORT IN SOUTH AMERICA.

Young Paul Vachet keeps saying it, he wants to e aviator !

Through determination, he obtains his military pilot's licence and is sent on perilous missionsover germany during the first world war.

After few years of "Civvy Steet", Paul joins the famous Latécoère Compagny (later to become Aérospatiale) and flies very soon on the Spanish routes which are reputed to be dangerous and sometimes lethal. He is later sent to South America to develop the aairlines for transporting mail. Paul vachet career will be marked by many spectacular accidents.

Complete story.
name: Vachet

description:
A rich, well-documented biography of the famous poet, author and aviator, Antoine de Saint-Exupéry. A tale that is all but banal !

The authors depict an unusual portrait of Antoine de Saint-Exupéry from his youth to the eve of his death. They relate the events that all know, such as his career in the Aéropostale, and his marriage with Consuelo de Saint-Exupéry, but also more secret facts: his interest in hypnosis, occultism or even the seaplane accident that nearly cost him his life.
name: Saint-Exupéry
Edouard Alfred Martel et l'incroyable découverte

description: THERE'S A BIG SURPRISE IN STORE IN VOLUME18! TWO SEPARATE STORIES, IN WHICH MARLENE AND LEO, TWO ODDBALLS WHO,TOGETHER, MAKE AN EVEN ODDER COUPLE, LEAD THE INVESTIGATION!A shooting right in the middle of a signing session in a bookstore? An escape in a hang-glider right in the centre of Marseilles? This is clearly a case for Leo Loden. A hostage-taking in the Bishop's Palace, the largest and most famous of the Marseilles police stations? Now here's a matter for Marlene Soral...
name: Tapas ou ça casse!!!

description:
FIRST INTERNATIONAL INVESTIGATION FOR OUR DETECTIVE!

Angouleme, the unforgiving world of graphic novels, where illustrators, scriptwriters, and editors meet at the end of January... as well as autograph hunters. Someone has stolen the story-boards of the brand new Lanfeust! Of course, this is a case for Leo. This new adventure will inevitably take him to the world capital of comics: Brussels!
name: Speculoos à la plancha

description:
INVESTIGATIONS TO PUT IN EVERYONE'S HANDS

A cop who becomes a private investigator, a girlfriend who remains in the policy and who would like to get married and a gallery of bad guys of all types... Crime novel, humour and sharp dialogue are the main points of this series.
name: Langoustines breizhées

description:
A NEW INVESTIGATION FOR LEO LODEN'S 20TH YEAR !

A seminar day on the Frioul archipelago brings together the executives of a pharmaceutical company...

The big boss is poisoned and dies during the cocktail party...

That is the perfect investigation for Leo, the perpetrator has to be on the island and it is not the ghost of the Count of Monte Cristo! But appearances might be deceiving...
name: Barigoule au Frioul
